Package algorithms

Class FixedSizeVector<T>

java.lang.Object
algorithms.FixedSizeVector<T>
Type Parameters:
T - class type to be held and sorted by this class. It must implement Comparable.
public class FixedSizeVector<T> extends Object
a class to hold a fixed number of items of type T. The latest capacity number of items are what is present in the vector. 
 runtime complexity is:
     O(1) for inserts, and gets
 Note that deletes are not allowed,
    but could be implemented in O(N) runtime.
 
 where N is the fixed capacity.
Author:
nichole

    • add

      public void add(T value)
      add value to the fixed size sorted list using (T).compareTo to order the items in the internal list. runtime complexity is O(log_2(capacity) + less than capacity).
      Parameters:
      value - value to insert into vector

    • size

      public int size()
      return the number of items in the internal array. if the array is not yet filled, the return will be less than the capacity, else will be the same as the capacity.
